					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Are you referring to the pitch of the generated waveform relative to the sample rate, or the sample rate that the operating system is actually using relative to the sample rate that you specified when opening an audio stream for output? For the former, you can add a feature to log sound output to a .wav file, and then count how many samples it takes for the waveform to rise and fall a given number of times. For the latter, you may have to use operating-system-specific APIs to determine the playback state of an output voice.<br /><br />Or are you referring to conversion of tone generator parameters to a musical pitch in A440 equal temperament tuning?</div>

